  <summary>4/15/1997--Introduced.
Family Tax Relief Act of 1997 - Amends the Internal Revenue Code to establish a credit of $500 multiplied by the number of qualifying children (under the age of 18) of a taxpayer. Reduces such credit if the taxpayer's income exceeds a threshold amount.</summary>
